scanning the target is the most important phase of information gathering it could be active or passive
active requires permission which means it directly interact with host to gain information....where as 
passive crawls the web for the information that is required:

1>ip gathering we can use tools like ping,nslookup,
 -->if we want to gather information about an ip 
 we use whois tool which gives full detailed information

2>technology fingerprintting on target using what web stealthy scan:
--->what web has a 1700 active plugins to identify the stack of technologies running behind
the target.

tip:to find the ip of ur router a verysimple cmd netstat -nr

#>nmap is the network mapper used to test the networks to find the open ports and 
then scans the services and further we should find the on what vulnerable programm its running

###########################################TCP SYN SCAN ########################################################################################
*tcp syn scan is the fastest scan it never estabilishes a full tcp connection and then fastest as it can scan 1000's of ports per second
only sends the first way of three way hand shake only sending syn................if the target sends the syn ack back then the target port is listening 
active and open

sudo nmap -sS 142.250.192.110
Starting Nmap 7.94SVN ( https://nmap.org ) at 2024-03-25 09:37 IST
Nmap scan report for bom12s17-in-f14.1e100.net (142.250.192.110)
