#########################################UDP SCAN #################################################################################################

sudo nmap -sU <ip>

########################################FINDING OS RUNNING BEHIND THE PORTS########################################################################
$ sudo nmap -0 192.168.1.1


########################################version of software running on a open port#################################################################

$ sudo nmap -0 192.168.1.1 -sV  --version-intensity(0 to 9) 9 

-A argument specifies the agression of the nmap scana by default scans the os and openports and version detection and enables nmap script scanning.
(dont use this on un permitted targets)

########################################filtering port range and output############################################################################
bypassing firewalls and ips and ids and also we use --script
even though we performed scans we can conceal our identity for geting idenfied as -f option should be used for not being identified
$ sudo nmap -F(faster first 100 ports) <ip>

firewall bypass:
filtered ports are the uncertain ports that cant be detiremined whether they are closed or open due to the presence of the firewalls...hence packet loss occurs thet firewall drops the packets

use -f to bypass(its sends the tiny ip fragmented packets it ) it splits the tcp headers into number of packets so that ids and firewalls cant detect the icmp packets. it splits each of the packet into 8 bytes

-f -f =16 
   splits pckates into 16 bytes...

  * if u want to increase fragemnt size --mtu 
##################################hiding ips using decoys############

sudo nmap -D RND:ip
 

 making this decoy scans can lets the server know its not only scanned by us.but also by decoys ids can report multiple ips are scanned the network not only the individual ip...they cant find which one is real